Description: A fragment of a jar-handle of pale grey-cream pottery, bearing an impressed cartouche on the original upper surface of a king Nekau, topped by the double plumed solar disk. The handle was probably one of a pair attached to a small amphora at either side of the neck.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (G), chamber 18
